# .dev.vars.example — the checked-in environment template (NO real secrets).
#
# One-command local dev: copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and set a real
# value, then `npm run dev`. The Cloudflare adapter's platformProxy loads `.dev.vars`
# and exposes these at `Astro.locals.runtime.env` for the /api/receipt boundary.
#
# In production the same variable is a Worker secret:
#   npx wrangler secret put DEMO_SIGNING_KEY
#
# Server-only signing key for the /api/receipt boundary. Never commit the real key.
DEMO_SIGNING_KEY="replace-with-a-long-random-string"

# Optional: put the boundary into a deliberate fault to watch `npm run ops:check`
# catch it. Leave unset for a healthy demo. 'broken' serves a signed note whose
# signature the check rejects; 'stalled' makes the boundary never answer, so the
# check fails at its time budget instead of spinning. (Anything else is treated as
# unset, so the server never breaks by accident.)
# DEMO_FAULT="broken"
